    "erz.eyebrow":"Small-group activity · about 15 minutes per card",
    "erz.h1":"Legal Ethics Scenario Randomizer",
    "erz.sub":"Draw a fictional AI-ethics dilemma from criminal defense practice, talk it through at your table, and share out. Every card ties back to a Texas Disciplinary Rule.",
    "erz.meta":"Texas Criminal Defense Lawyers Association · Facilitator <a href=\"mailto:mguhlin@tcea.org\">Miguel Guhlin</a> · Adapted for the defense from a Think-Pair-Share tabletop set (CC&nbsp;BY-SA), inspired by the OECD Ethics of AI discussion flashcards",
